<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1330,1716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1610,1636]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
Collected from several stations off 
<collectingRegion box="[751,822,1610,1636]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[836,1007,1610,1636]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1073,1249,1610,1636]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, at depths from 
<quantity box="[151,334,1650,1676]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6985" metricValueMax="2.239" metricValueMin="1.158" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" unit="m" value="1698.5" valueMax="2239.0" valueMin="1158.0">1158 to 2239 m</quantity>
(depth record). Previously reported in Brazilian waters to north of Vitória-Trindade Seamount Chain, at 
<quantity box="[264,338,1690,1716]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.37" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" unit="m" value="637.0">637 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Seret, B. &amp; Andreata, J. V." box="[425,703,1690,1716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" pagination="81 - 100" refId="ref18331" refString="Seret, B. &amp; Andreata, J. V. (1992) Deep-sea fishes collected during cruise MD- 55 off Brazil. Cybium, 16 (1), 81 - 100." type="journal article" year="1992">Séret &amp; Andreata 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
